text: KAJF-LD is a digital low-powered television station licensed to Topeka, Kansas. The station is owned by DTV America Corporation or Sunrise, Florida, and the station broadcasts is digital signal on UHF channel 17 (or virtual channel 21 via PSIP). The signal originates from a transmitter on the southeast side of Kansas City, Missouri just off 58th Street near the Exit 65 interchange of Interstate 435.http://rabbitears.info/contour.php?appid=2002395 The station's main channel was Silent, but has since picked up The Country Network. The subchannels serve as affiliates of GetTV, the Sonlife Broadcasting Network, Shop LC, LXTV, QVC, and OnTV4U respectively.Digital TV Market Listing for KAJF-LD (Kansas City, MO market).
